.TH "sg_alloc_table" 9 "sg_alloc_table" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sg_alloc_table \- Allocate and initialize an sg table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sg_alloc_table
.BI "(struct sg_table *table "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nents "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "table" 12
The sg table header to use
.IP "nents" 12
Number of entries in sg list
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
GFP allocation mask
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate and initialize an sg table. If \fInents\fP\fI\fP is larger than
SG_MAX_SINGLE_ALLOC a chained sg table will be setup.
